Pre-Game Insights: Honduras needs to secure a victory against Jamaica to move closer to qualifying for the quarterfinals, where the United States, Mexico, Canada, and Panama are already waiting.
The match will be held at José de la Paz Herrera 'Chelato' Uclés Stadium in Tegucigalpa, Honduras, on September 10, 2024, at 20:00-08:00 PM.
Honduras previously faced Jamaica in the 2023-24 edition of the Concacaf Nations League, where Jamaica won 1-0 at Independence Park in Kingston.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match will be broadcasted on various channels including Canal 8 & Canal 20, TSi & Canal DEPORTES TVC in Honduras, Televisa in Mexico, CBS, Paramount+, TUDN, and Telemundo in the United States, and Concacaf GO & YouTube Concacaf for the rest of the world.
